children.text: The chipboard sheet flooring has not been fixed into the joists sufficiently, with fixings spaced at greater than the maximum allowable centres.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, clause 5.5.4.3. Particleboard Fixing requires that

‘sheets shall be securely glued and nailed to the top edge of the joists. Nails shall be 10mm from all edges and at 150mm centres at end and butt joints for square edge sheets. Nails shall be at 300 mm max. centres at intermediate joists’ .
These sheets need to be properly fixed to the joists at no greater than 150mm centres along the joins, and 300mm centres at intermediate joists.
